{
    "code": "012", 
    "data": "At performing the ritual ablution, it is necessary to sit down, face the kiblah direction, and put the bowl (containing the water of ablution) to the right side. Upon looking at the water, it is recommended to say the following:\nاَلْحَمْدُ لِلهِ الَّذِيْ جَعَلَ الْمَاءَ طَهُورًا\nALHAMDO LILLAAHIL LAZEE JA-A’LAL MAA-A TAHOORAN\nAll praise be to Allah Who has made water pure\nوَ لَمْ يَجْعَلْهُ نَجِسًا\nWA LAM YAJ-A’LHO NAJESAN\nbut has not made it impure.\nBefore putting the hand in the bowl, it is recommended to wash it. At putting it there, it is recommended to say the following:\nبِسْمِ اللهِ وَ بِاللهِ\nBISMILLAAHE WA BILLAAHE\nIn the Name of Allah (I begin) and in Allah (I trust).\nاَللّٰهُمَّ اجْعَلْنِيْ مِنَ التَّوَّابِيْنَ\nALLAAHUMMAJ A’LNEE MENAT TAWWAABEENA\nO Allah, make me of those who turn much to You \nوَ اجْعَلْنِيْ مِنَ الْمُتَطَهِّرِيْنَ\nWAJ A’LNEE MENAL MOTATAHHEREENA\nand make me of those who purify themselves.\nYou may then rinse out your mouth with three handfuls of water three times and say the following:\nاَللّٰهُمَّ لَقِّنِيْ حُجَّتِيْ يَوْمَ اَلْقَاكَ\nALLAAHUMMA LAQQENEE HUJJAATEE YAWMA ALQAKA\nO Allah, (please) make me receive my proof on the Day when I will meet You \nوَ اَطْلِقْ لِسَانِيْ بِذِكْرِكَ\nWA ATLIQ LESAANEE BEZIKREKA\nand cause my tongue to be eloquent with mention of You.\nYou may then inhale water (from the nose) three times and say the following:\nاَللّٰهُمَّ لَا تُحَرِّمْ عَلَيَّ رِيْحَ الْجَنَّةِ\nALLAAHUMMA LAA TOHARRIM A’LAYYA REEHAL JANNATE\nO Allah, do not ban me from (smelling) the scent of Paradise;\nوَ اجْعَلْنِيْ مِمَّنْ يَشَمُّ رِيْـحَهَا\nWAJ A’LNEE MIMMAN YASHAMMO REEHAHAA\nrather, make me of those who smell its scent,\nوَ رَوْحَهَا وَ طِيْبَهَا\nWA RAWHAHAA WA TEEBAHAA\nnice breathe, and fragrance.\nYou may then begin with washing the face, saying the following:\nاَللّٰهُمَّ بَيِّضْ وَجْهِيْ يَوْمَ تَسْوَدُّ الْوُجُوْهُ\nALLAAHUMMA BAYYIZ WAJHEE YAWMA TASWADDUL WOJOOHO\nO Allah, (please) whiten my face on the day when faces will turn black\nوَ لَا تُسَوِّدْ وَجْهِيْ يَوْمَ تَبْيَضُّ الْوُجُوْهُ\nWA LAA TOSAWWID WAJHEE YAWMA TABYAZZUL WOJOOHO\nand do not blacken my face on the day when (other) faces will turn white.\nYou may then take a handful of water to wash your right hand, saying the following:\nاَللّٰهُمَّ اَعْطِنِيْ كِتَابِيْ بِيَمِيْنِيْ\nALLAAHUMMA AA’TENEE KETAABEE BEYAMEENEE\nO Allah, (please) give me my Record (of deeds) in my right hand\nوَ الْخُلْدَ فِيْ الْجِنَانِ بِيَسَارِيْ\nWAL KHULDA FIL JENAANE BEYASAAREE\nand immortality in the gardens of Paradise in my left hand,\nوَ حَاسِبْنِيْ حِسَابًا يَسِيْرًا\nWA HAASIBNEE HESAABAN YASEERAN\nand make me take my account by an easy reckoning.\nYou may then wash your left hand and say the following:\nاَللّٰهُمَّ لَا تُعْطِنِيْ كِتَابِيْ بِشِمَالِيْ\nALLAAHUMMA LAA TO’TENEE KETAABEE BESHEMAALEE\nO Allah, do not give me my Record of Deeds in my left hand\nوَ لَا مِنْ وَرَاءِ ظَهْرِيْ\nWA LAA MIN WARAAE ZAHREE\nnor from my back;\nوَ لَا تَجْعَلْهَا مَغْلُولَةً اِلٰى عُنُقِيْ\nWA LAA TAJ-A’LHAA MAGHLOOLATAN ELAA O’NOQEE\nand do not cause my hand to be chained to my neck.\nوَ اَعُوْذُ بِكَ مِنْ مُقَطَّعَاتِ النِّيْـرَانِ\nWA A-O’OZO BEKA MIN MOQATTE-A’ATIN NEERAANE\nI also pray Your protection against the severing flames of Hellfire.\nYou may then rub the forepart of your head with your wetted forefingers of your right hand and say the following:\nاَللّٰهُمَّ غَشِّنِيْ رَحْمَتَكَ وَ بَرَكَاتِكَ\nALLAAHUMMA GHASHSHENEE RAHMATAKA WA BARAKAATEKA\nO Allah, (please) overshadow me with Your mercy and blessings.\nYou may then rub your feet, saying the following:\nاَللّٰهُمَّ ثَبِّتْنِيْ عَلٰى الصِّرَاطِ\nALLAAHUMMA SABBITNEE A’LAS SERAATE\nO Allah, (please) make me stand firm on the Discriminating Bridge\nيَوْمَ تَزِلُّ الْاَقْدَامُ\nYAWMA TAZILLUL AQDAAMO\non the day when the feet will slip\nوَ اجْعَلْ سَعْيِيْ فِيْمَا يُرْضِيْكَ عَنِّيْ\nWAJ A’L SA’YEE FEEMAA YURZEEKA A’NNEE\nand cause all my efforts to be in what brings about Your satisfaction with me.\nيَا ذَا الْجَلَالِ وَ الْاِكْرَامِ\nYAA ZAL JALAALE WAL IKRAAME.\nO Lord of Majesty and Honoring!\nUpon accomplishment of the ritual ablution, you may say the following:\nاَللّٰهُمَّ اِنِّيْ اَسْاَلُكَ تَمَامَ الْوُضُوءِ\nALLAAHUMMA INNEE AS-ALOKA TAMAAMALWUZOO-E\nO Allah, I beseech You for perfect ablution,\nوَ تَمَامَ الصَّلَاةِ\nWA TAMAAMAS SALAATE\nperfect prayer,\nوَ تَمَامَ رِضْوَانِكَ وَ الْجَنَّةَ\nWA TAMAAMA RIZWAANEKA WAL JANNAATA\nperfect pleasure of You, and Paradise.\nYou may also say the following:\nاَلْحَمْدُ لِلهِ رَبِّ الْعَالَمِيْنَ\nALHAMDO LILLAAHE RABBIL A’ALAMEEN.\nAll praise be to Allah, the Lord of the Worlds.\nUpon accomplishment too, you may recite Surah al-Qadr (No. 97) three times and impart a sweet smell to yourself.", 
    "title": "Ritual Ablution (Wuzu)"
}